title._content: Trefaldighetskyrkan (Holy Trinity Church), Karlskrona, Blekinge, Sweden

description._content: Trefaldighetskyrkan (Holy Trinity Church) with bell tower at the Main Square in Karlskrona. The Baroque church, built in 1750, was created by Nicodemus Tessin the Younger and recreated by architect Olof Tempelman after the city fire in 1790. The church is also called the German Church since it originally was the church of the German congregation in Karlskrona. Trefaldighetskyrkan med klocktorn vid Stortorget i Karlskrona. Barockkyrkan, byggd 1750, ritades av Nicodemus Tessin den yngre och återskapades av arkitekt Olof Tempelman efter stadsbranden 1790. Kyrkan kallas också Tyska kyrkan eftersom den ursprungligen var kyrka för den tyska församlingen i Karlskrona.
